Seven passengers were injured after a taxi overturned on
Crocodile Road in Waterloo, KwaZulu Natal. “Members of Reaction Unit South Africa were called out to
the scene by the public requesting assistance for the injured. Upon arrival the taxi was found lying on its roof. Seven passengers
sustained minor to moderate injuries,” RUSA spokesperson Prem Balram said. According to Balram, they were treated on scene by before
being transported to Osindisweni Hospital. Balram said it’s alleged that the taxi was travelling down
Tiger Road when its brakes failed. “In an attempt to stop the vehicle the driver turned onto
Crocodile Road causing the vehicle to overturn and land on a bus shelter,’ Balram
added. 